docs.abstract: The void is as old as time, but it was a human innovation to harness it with a symbol.
docs.snippet: The void is as old as time, but it was a human innovation to harness it with a symbol.
docs.lead_paragraph: Carbon dating of an ancient Indian document, the Bakhshali manuscript, has recently placed the first written occurrence of the number zero in the third or fourth century A.D., about 500 years earlier than previously believed. While the news has no practical bearing on the infrastructure of zeros (and ones) underlying our high-tech civilization, it does remind us how indebted we are for this invention. But to whom is this debt owed? And how should it be repaid?
